p: \r...you again. From the Suntouched Gym, right?
\bPleased to see you again, Harmony. You too \pn, Nora.
\bMy name's Taen, if you don't remember. I'm a part of Perfection.
\rDon't worry, you're hard to forget about.
\rYou, at the back! I don't know why you're tampering with our power, but you better start explainin'!
\bDon't worry, Harmony, we'll turn the power back on.
\bWe just want to talk to you, that's all.
\rReukra? What... what are you doing?\nWhy are you here?
\bI want to make a deal with you, Harmony.
\rA deal? What are you talking about?
\bI'll put the power back on in good faith.
\bIt's been a while, hasn't it?
\bWhen was the last time I saw you? College graduation?
\bI've been looking for you for a while, but also one of your patients.
\bSpecifically, the one who's name is "Malde".
\rWhat? That's my father.\nWhat do you want with him?
\bWe want to help, Harmony.
\bWe're not as bad as you think.
\bWe know he's sick, and we know you want the best for him.
\bLet us help you. We can both get what we want here.
\bLet's go to his room so we can talk more. Go to Malde's room on the top floor, and we can talk.
\rFine, whatever. Let's get this over with.
\bVery well.
\bNow, follow me.
\rYou used to be so... different.
\r...what.
\rWho's this "Malde" guy? How does Harmony know a cultist?
\bNo clue, but I'm planning on following them.
\b\pn, you should come along. I'd love to have some support.
\rHe's still not talking to me after what I said...
\rI can't blame him. What I said was awful.\nI just hope that he won't snap and betray us.
\rWait up, I'm coming!
